            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "No, you are not supposed to run untrusted template code. So the \"mitigation\" is to never pass user-provided code to `render_template_string()` or put untrusted code into a template file.\r\n\r\nThe post you linked actually mentions this:\r\n\r\n> Ultimately, it is up to the developers using these frameworks to properly follow template design best practices and ensure that their applications do not blindly trust user-supplied data."
